    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.55.1" />
                
                <fw type="curtorial"><del/>1</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        5835 Vine Street
                        Lincoln, Nebraska 68505
                        April 1, 1968
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. Slade Kendrick</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>225 Willard Way</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Ithaca, New York</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Slade:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Another bully letter from you!</p>
                
                <p>Since I wrote you last some nice things have been happening. First of all, the University of Missouri will give me the Thomas Jefferson Award on April 12. This is a much coveted honor, as I have no doubt you know. Then on April 20 there will be a ceremony at the University Library dedicating the Neihardt Collection and the bronze bust which has been mounted on a marble pedestal.</p>
                
                <p>I am leaving Wednesday for Columbia. On the 5th of April I will hold forth at a banquet given in memory of Rose O'Neill whose home was near Branson and whom we knew well. You will remember her as the maker kewpies<sic>maker of kewpies</sic>. She was also a very fine lyric poet, which is something the public doesn't know.</p>
                
                <p>I am glad you have been reading Pliny. His description of the destruction of Pompeii is of course a classic.</p>
                
                <p>I am looking forward to seeing my family and I consider my dogs a part of the family. One expects a family to hug him but the way these doggies go on when I come home is enough to make one want to weep.</p>
                
                <p>I am moving under full sail with my old man's rememberings. I really wish I did not have to go away just now. I'd like to continue with the writing. Slade, I wouldn't be surprised if it would be a pretty fair book. Anyway, it's fun to write.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With affectionate thoughts for you and your lady,</salute>
                
                    <signed>John</signed>
                    <signed>John</signed>
                
                    <note>JGN:nh</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
